               <msContents>
                  <summary>This papyrus contains two separate receipts. The first receipt is for military clothing and signed by the secretary of the fullers' guild. Only three lines survive of the second receipt, but it is clear that it is concerned with the collocation of two charges: the epikephalaion and the primipilon.</summary>
